        "content": "<p>Hello! This seemingly simple problem has me stumped. I have a function that is strictly monotone, and a set defined by evaluating that function over the natural numbers. Surely this set is infinite, because there is an injective function <code>x =&gt; f x</code>, which must be injective because <code>f</code> is strictly monotone. I'm struggling to find the right lemmas in Mathlib to make this argument! Here's a MWE:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">StrictMono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">π</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Infinite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
